  <section>
    <num>1.1</num>
    <heading>Short Title</heading>
    <text><cite path="">This enactment</cite> shall be known as the "Kiowa Tribe Annual Budget Appropriation for Fiscal Year 2026-2027".</text>
  </section>
  <section>
    <num>1.2</num>
    <heading>Purpose</heading>
    <text>The purpose of the Act is to approve a "Kiowa Tribe Annual Budget Appropriation for Fiscal Year 2026-2027", for the Tribe, subject to final approval by the voters.</text>
  </section>
  <section>
    <num>1.3</num>
    <heading>Findings</heading>
    <text>The Legislature hereby finds and declares that:</text>
    <para>
      <num>(a)</num>
      <text>The Legislature is vested with the authority to pass an Annual Budget, and budget modifications, for the Tribe, subject to approval by the voters.</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(b)</num>
      <text>The Kiowa Constitution, which requires an annual budget and any budget modifications, to be approved by the Legislature and Chairman, with final approval by the voters.</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(c)</num>
      <text>The Legislature has identified the need to enact the "Kiowa Tribe Annual Budget Appropriation for Fiscal Year 2026-2027" to include unidentified revenue and expenditures, including newly received funds and to address additional funding needs.</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(d)</num>
      <text>The Tribe shall operate on a fiscal year beginning July 1<sup>st</sup> and ending June 30<sup>th</sup>, <cite doc="Constitution of the Kiowa Tribe">Article 6, Section 6 (v)</cite> The Legislature shall have the power to raise revenue and appropriate funds for expenditure.  Every funding item in an annual budget must have been previously authorized by law.  No monies shall be drawn from the Treasury except by signature of the Chairman and except upon authorization and appropriation by law, (vi) if the Legislature fails to approve an annual budget within sixty days of presentment of a proposed annual budget by the Chairman to the Legislature by February 1<sup>st</sup>, then the annual budget presented by the Chairman shall be deemed approved for the purpose of placing such budget before the voters for approval or disapproval.  If a new annual budget is not approved by the beginning of the fiscal year, then the most recently approved budget shall remain in effect until a new budget is approved. (2026-2027)</text>
    </para>
  </section>
